  "text": "The Envoy HTTP filter configuration propagation begins with the protobuf definition in data-plane-api and flows through multiple C++ components in envoy:\n\n**Protobuf Definition (data-plane-api):**\nThe `HttpConnectionManager` message is defined in `envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto` (line 43). This message contains a field `http_filters` (line 471) which is a repeated list of `HttpFilter` messages (line 1339). Each `HttpFilter` (lines 1338-1380+) contains a `name` field and a `oneof config_type` that can be either a `typed_config` (google.protobuf.Any containing filter-specific configuration) or a `config_discovery` for dynamic configuration.\n\n**Configuration Factory (envoy - config.h):**\nThe `HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory` class (lines 53-71 in config.h) is responsible for parsing the protobuf configuration. It extends `Common::ExceptionFreeFactoryBase<HttpConnectionManager>` and implements the `createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped` method which accepts the protobuf HttpConnectionManager message.\n\n**Configuration Processing (envoy - config.cc):**\nThe `HttpConnectionManagerConfig` constructor (lines 709-743 in config.cc) receives the protobuf HttpConnectionManager configuration. At line 709-712, it creates a `FilterChainHelper` instance templated with `Server::Configuration::FactoryContext` and `Server::Configuration::NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory`. At line 714, the constructor calls `helper.processFilters(config.http_filters(), \"http\", \"http\", filter_factories_)` to process the filter chain.\n\n**Filter Chain Processing (envoy - filter_chain_helper.h):**\nThe `FilterChainHelper` class (lines 69-201 in filter_chain_helper.h) is a template that processes HTTP filter configurations. Its `processFilters` method (lines 87-102) iterates through the repeated `HttpFilter` messages from the protobuf. For each filter, it calls the private `processFilter` method (lines 106-165) which:\n1. Extracts the filter name and configuration\n2. Looks up the corresponding C++ filter factory using the filter name\n3. Translates the protobuf configuration to the factory-specific protobuf message\n4. Calls the factory's `createFilterFactoryFromProto` method to instantiate the filter\n5. Registers the filter in the list of active filters, respecting the `disabled_by_default` flag and handling dynamic config discovery\n\n**Connection Manager Integration (envoy - conn_manager_impl.h/cc and conn_manager_config.h):**\nThe `ConnectionManagerConfig` interface (conn_manager_config.h) and `ConnectionManagerImpl` implementation (conn_manager_impl.h/cc) use the filter factories created by the above process. The `FilterChainFactory::createFilterChain` method (implemented by HttpConnectionManagerConfig) applies these filters to actual HTTP connections.\n\n**Data Flow Summary:**\nProtobuf HttpConnectionManager message → HttpConnectionManagerFilterConfigFactory → HttpConnectionManagerConfig constructor → FilterChainHelper::processFilters() → Individual HttpFilter processing → Filter factories instantiation → Filter chain for connection handling"
